Actress Sandra Bullock has given one million dollars to the American Red Cross to boost its tsunami relief campaign, the organisation said Monday. ``Sandra continues to enable our lifesaving work and is a model for personal generosity,'' said Marsha J. Evans, the American Red Cross president. Plans are in the works for several big concerts, with the proceeds going to various charities involved in the tsunami relief effort. Among the stars who will take part are : Avril Lavigne, Sarah McLachlan, Sum 41 and the Barenaked Ladies. 